list.comment:
feat: add findDuplicate and pyramid methods in Main.java (main)
This commit adds two new methods to the Main.java file:
- findDuplicate method that takes an int array as input and returns true if it contains any duplicate elements, false otherwise - pyramid method that takes an int n as input and prints a pyramid of n stars
The commit also refactors some existing code in the Main.java file:
- Comment out some unused method calls in the main method - Update the workspace.xml file with the latest changelist and task information
The issue number is obtained from the branch name, which is main.

task.summary:
feat: add .idea, .gitignore and Main.java files (main)
This commit adds the following files to the project:
- .idea/vcs.xml: contains the mapping of the project directory to Git - .idea/misc.xml: contains the project settings such as JDK version and output directory - .idea/modules.xml: contains the module information for the project - .idea/workspace.xml: contains the workspace settings such as changelist and task manager - .gitignore: contains the files and directories to be ignored by Git - beginer-question.iml: contains the module type and source folder for the project - src/Main.java: contains the main class with some methods for printing numbers, multiplication table and finding maximum value in an array
The issue number is obtained from the branch name, which is main.

feat: add reverseArray method and refactor code in Main.java (main)
This commit adds a new method to reverse an array and refactors some existing code in the Main.java file. The changes are:
- Add reverseArray method that takes an int array as input and returns a new array with the elements in reverse order - Use reverseArray method in the main method to print the reversed array - Format the code with spaces and comments for readability - Remove unused imports and variables - Update the workspace.xml file with the latest changelist and task information
The issue number is obtained from the branch name, which is main.

feat: add addUpTo and position methods in Main.java (main)
This commit adds two new methods to the Main.java file:
- addUpTo method that takes an int n as input and returns the sum of all integers from 1 to n - position method that takes a String string as input and prints the first uppercase letter and its index, or -1 if none
The commit also refactors some existing code in the Main.java file:
- Remove unused imports and variables - Format the code with spaces and comments for readability - Update the workspace.xml file with the latest changelist and task information
The issue number is obtained from the branch name, which is main.
